Consider the following C code segment.
a = b + c;
e = a + 1;
d = b + c;
f = d + 1;
g = e + f;
In a compiler, this code segment is represented internally as a directed acyclic graph (DAG). The number of nodes in the DAG is ________.
[GATE 2021|| SET-1 NAT || 1-mark]

questions.explanation:
Follow(B) = First(D) Union Follow(A)
{Follow(B) = Follow(A) when D is epsilon}
Follow(B) = {d} Union {a} = {a,d}
Hence Answer is : 31

In the production: P → xQRS,
FOLLOW (Q) = FIRST (R)
FIRST (R) = {w, ϵ} >br> Since FIRST (R) = {ϵ}, so FOLLOW (Q) → {w} ∪ FIRST(S)
FIRST(S) = {y}
So, FOLLOW (Q) = {w, y}

